ssion copy scans against real decision windows to see whether clustered-copy ever appears during tradable hours, or whether it is mostly a post-session phenomenon that should only modulate after-hours inference.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 22:59 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] V7b Copy-Cluster Guard Spec Written\n\n**Task:** Turn the new PM copy-cluster findings into a deployable strategy artifact so the next coding pass can implement the guardrail directly instead of reconstructing it from notes.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains correctly flat outside active hours.\n- I wrote a new secondary strategy spec at `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7b-copy-cluster-guard.spec.md`.\n- The spec defines a measurable clustered-copy regime using:\n  - `dominant_title_share >= 0.40` or\n  - `dominant_triple_share >= 0.40`\n- It explicitly frames the feature as a **risk-off guardrail**, not a directional trigger.\n- It also defines a conservative rollout path: first expose metrics and shadow-log the flag, then consider conviction reduction or churn-blo",
